description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric Bladder and Bowel Service&lt;br /&gt;BAND 6&lt;br /&gt;LOCATION Covering Wiltshire. 30hrs per week  Base address is Trowbridge/Chippenham/Salisbury tbc&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a caring, forward thinking, dynamic nurse who is committed to providing child centred holistic support to children and young people with Bladder and Bowel Dysfunction? Due to an opening we are looking for Band 6 Nurse to join the   Children’s Bladder and Bowel Service in Wiltshire .  Are you looking to join an NHS Health and Social Care partner which is striving to make positive changes? Would you like to work for an organisation where more than 9 out of every ten 10 of the people who use services would recommend them?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel Valued&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a nurse with services with&lt;strong&gt; Paediatric Bladder and Bowel Service&lt;/strong&gt; you will receive AFC  salary including NHS pension. We’ll provide you with access to a committed Learning and Development team, and we work closely with you to further your potential and support your progression. We will offer a combination of in house eLearning, workshops and courses to support your development, including the chance to complete a Leadership/Management Apprenticeship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will become part of the Virgin Tribe. Where you can receive discounts on Virgin Products such as holidays and experience days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll access our central online health and lifestyle platform covering healthy recipes, activity challenges, and support information around mental health. You will have access to Mind Coach and Type Coach Workshops to support your well-being we also provide Restorative Supervision.Feel Proud&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a Children’s nursing qualification – RSCN/RN Child branch or Specialist Practitioner or have relevant experience in this field&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a small team of Nurses, who work closely together to promote a healthy happy working environment where everyone can reach their full potential and are looking to develop and expand the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Band 6 Nurse you will be delivering high quality, evidence based assessments to support children/young people with Bladder and Bowel Dysfunction to achieve their full potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working closely with families, schools and carers and the wider multi-disciplinary team to promote healthy Bladder and Bowels to all service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive regular 1:1 supervision and appraisals with your Line Manager. As a team we will get together regularly, auditing and sharing skills and knowledge. You will be a part of quality improvements, research and development activity, which includes the opportunity to link in with local and National Forums. Here we recognise and celebrate clinical excellence and dedication &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel the difference&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’d like to discuss the role further, or request the full job description, please contact Joanne Conroy via email (joanne.conroy@virgincare.co.uk) or by telephone – 07976752156.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re welcome to come in for an informal visit, meet our friendly team and ask any queries you may have before you apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We partner with the NHS to make a real difference to people in Wiltshire and B&amp;NES and we’re building a working environment where colleagues too can really feel the difference. It’s the kind of place where nothing’s too much trouble. Where you’ll feel empowered, listened to, valued and where we’ll support you to bring your best self to work every single day and to deliver high quality care. And that’s just the beginning. We deliver services to millions of people by developing our own unique approach where our patients are at the centre of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re committed to equal opportunities and welcome a broad diversity of talent to apply. We reserve the right to cease any advertising prior to the published closing date for a role that receives a high number of applications. Virgin Care Limited, its subsidiary companies and the Virgin Care LLPs are part of the Virgin Group and provide NHS and social care services. If you would like to know a little more about how we use your information, please see our website’s privacy policy.&lt;/p&gt;
